<refentry id="bif.ArgMax" xreflabel="ArgMax">

<refmeta>
<indexterm>
<primary>ArgMax</primary>
</indexterm>

<refentrytitle>ArgMax</refentrytitle>
<refmiscinfo>Built-in function</refmiscinfo>
</refmeta>

<refnamediv>
<refname>ArgMax</refname>
<refpurpose>
Returns the index of a maximal element of a list 
</refpurpose>
</refnamediv>

<refsynopsisdiv>
<synopsis>
ArgMax[x->LIST(NUMBER)] =: INTEGER 
</synopsis>
</refsynopsisdiv>

<refsect1><title>Description</title>
<para>
<function>ArgMax</function>
returns the index of the first element of the list <parameter>x</parameter> which
attains the maximum value of any elements in the list.  
</para>
</refsect1>

</refentry>

